member.remarks:
            The standard usage of this tool requires the following steps:
            

connect to a DB (using frmLogin);

select a process operation;

select the run;

type in the event # and push Enter;

select the elements to display and choose the appropriate colors. 
            
            Double-clicking on an element displays information about it.

The path view is a 3D view provided by GDI3D and its Display Control.

By dragging the image with the right mouse button pressed, one can rotate/pan it.

Default points of view are available (XY, YZ, XZ).

To center the view on a particularly interesting point, click on Set Focus and then left-click on the interesting point.

The image obtained can be saved to an X3L file, and/or it can be merged with an X3L file. This is typically used to overlap the scanback/scanoforth history with TotalScan results.
